fields.description:
h5.Summary
The iOS version of "ti.map" module's {{View}} type has a {{zoom()}} method that is missing on Android. We should add this {{View.zoom()}} method for parity.

The module's docs do not indicate that the {{zoom()}} function is Android only. This suggests that it's cross-platform, which is wrong.

h5.Work-Around
Currently, the only method that supports zooming on Android and iOS is {{View.setLocation()}} via its "latitudeDelta" and "longitudeDelta" settings.

h5.Steps to reproduce:
1. Use the code below in your app.js:
{code}
var MapModule = require('ti.map');

var win = Ti.UI.createWindow({fullscreen: false, layout: "vertical"});
 
var map = MapModule.createView({
    enableZoomControls: false,
    mapType: MapModule.NORMAL_TYPE,
    animate: true,
});
 
var b4 = Ti.UI.createButton({
    title: "Zoom in/out"
});
var zoomLevel = 1;
b4.addEventListener('click', function(){
    map.zoom(zoomLevel);
    zoomLevel = -zoomLevel;
});

win.add(b4);
win.add(map);
win.open();
{code}
2. Setup your app for using android map module.
3. Build for device/emulator.
4. After the app launches tap on {{ZOOM IN/OUT}}.
